messages.content:
it seems some of the data loads only after scrolling into place. see if you can pass browserActions params into bin/fetch (from Scrappey docs:
curl -X POST "https://publisher.scrappey.com/api/v1?key=API_KEY" \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{
    "cmd": "request.get",
    "url": "https://example.com",
    "browserActions": [
      {
        "type": "scroll",
        "cssSelector": "#bottomElement",
        "repeat": 3,
        "delayMs": 1000
      }
    ]
  }'
)
